D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-resignation-berkshire-hathaway-shareholder-meeting-omaha-nfm-brooks-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOracle%20of%20Omaha%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20a%20role%20model%20for%20countless%20investors%20throughout%20his%20career%2C%20with%20fans%20regarding%20him%20as%20a%20father%20figure%2C%20teacher%2C%20and%20value-investing%20legend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett's%20decision%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-meeting-resignation-audience-reaction-legacy-career-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estep%20down%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20that%20he%20purchased%20in%201965%20and%20transformed%20from%20a%20struggling%20textile%20mill%20into%20a%20%241%20trillion-plus%20powerhouse%20%E2%80%94%20marks%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-biographer-alice-schroeder-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eend%20of%20an%20era%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Berkshire's%20Class%20A%20stock%20has%20returned%20over%205%2C500%2C000%25%20over%20six%20decades%2C%20or%20roughly%2020%25%20a%20year%2C%20against%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500's%2039%2C000%25%20increase%20over%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20obviously%20a%20legend%20in%20our%20lifetimes%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20Crowell%2C%20the%20vice%20chairman%20of%20wealth%20management%20at%20DA%20Davidson%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20market%20experts%20to%20everyday%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-steps-down-berkshire-hathaway-business-leaders-react-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuffett's%20legacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20touched%20generations%20of%20investors.%20Here%20are%20five%20takeaways%20from%20Buffett's%20career%20that%20you%20can%20use%20in%20your%20own%20investing%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a48de7c2-ace3-4843-b6d6-bc926f70f726%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Buy%20businesses%2C%20not%20stocks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20pillars%20to%20Buffett's%20success%20is%20thinking%20like%20a%20long-term%20business%20owner%2C%20not%20a%20speculative%20stock%20picker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20aren't%20willing%20to%20own%20a%20stock%20for%2010%20years%2C%20don't%20even%20think%20about%20owning%20it%20for%2010%20minutes%2C%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20said%20in%20his%201996%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-write-like-warren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-shareholder-letter-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%20to%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20shareholders%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20conceptualize%20when%20you're%20transacting%20on%20Robinhood%2C%20but%20when%20you%20buy%20a%20company's%20stock%2C%20you're%20becoming%20a%20stakeholder%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20who%20owns%20a%20piece%20of%20a%20real%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20just%20buying%20a%20ticker%20symbol.%20You're%20actually%20a%20partial%20owner%20in%20a%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Crowell%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20friend%20of%20yours%20asked%20you%20to%20invest%20%245%2C000%20in%20their%20business%2C%20you%20would%20think%20about%20it%20as%20well%3A%20Who%20is%20this%20friend%3F%20How%20qualified%20are%20they%3F%20What%20does%20this%20business%20look%20like%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20investors%20should%20dig%20into%20how%20a%20company%20actually%20makes%20its%20money.%20Think%20about%20a%20company's%20management%20team%2C%20brand%20strength%2C%20and%20competitive%20advantage%20when%20you%20buy%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22439b899a-79ee-4180-8e51-be65ff069c4c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Invest%20in%20what%20you%20understand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20and%20his%20business%20partner%20Charlie%20Munger%20popularized%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bcircle%20of%20competence%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20mental%20framework%20that%20encourages%20investors%20to%20invest%20in%20businesses%20or%20industries%20that%20they%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20OK%20if%20you're%20circle%20is%20small%20%E2%80%94%20what's%20more%20important%20is%20understanding%20how%20the%20businesses%20within%20it%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20famously%20avoided%20tech%20stocks%20for%20most%20of%20his%20career%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20didn't%20understand%20the%20industry%20well%20enough%20to%20value%20them.%20It%20wasn't%20until%202016%20that%20Buffett%20bought%20into%20Apple%2C%20which%20has%20since%20grown%20to%20be%20Berkshire's%20largest%20holding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20changed%3F%20Buffett%20invested%20in%20Apple%20because%20he%20viewed%20it%20as%20a%20durable%20consumer%20brand%20with%20a%20high%20customer%20retention%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20understand%20the%20phone%20at%20all%2C%20but%20I%20do%20understand%20consumer%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20Buffett%20said%20at%20Berkshire%20Hathaway's%20annual%20shareholder%20meeting%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThinking%20about%20investing%20in%20bitcoin%20because%20it's%20all%20over%20the%20news%3F%20Hopping%20on%20the%20AI%20trend%20even%20though%20you%20have%20no%20idea%20how%20the%20technology%20works%3F%20Forget%20about%20it%2C%20according%20to%20Buffett.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22825f8aa7-4af2-4e8a-bd8b-135462a7a0b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20FOMO%20is%20your%20biggest%20enemy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tempting%20to%20hop%20aboard%20popular%20trades%2C%20but%20Buffett's%20track%20record%20shows%20that%20it%20does%20pay%20off%20to%20be%20fearful%20when%20everyone%20else%20is%20being%20greedy%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20everybody%20wants%20in%20on%20it%2C%20that's%20probably%20not%20the%20right%20time%20to%20jump%20in.%20You're%20probably%20overpaying%20for%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Crowell%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%