%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20concerned%20about%20running%20out%20of%20money%20%E2%80%94%20and%20younger%20generations%20are%20more%20bothered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllianz%20Life%20surveyed%201%2C000%20individuals%20age%2025%2B%20living%20in%20the%20contiguous%20US%20for%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allianzlife.com%2Fabout%2Fnewsroom%2F2025-Press-Releases%2FAmericans-Are-More-Worried-About-Running-Out-of-Money-Than-Death%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2025%20Annual%20Retirement%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E.%2070%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20fear%20going%20broke%20before%20they%20die%2C%20while%2061%25%20of%20boomers%20reported%20the%20same%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGenXers%20are%20really%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20coming%20up%20to%20the%20danger%20zone%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20LaVigne%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20consumer%20insights%20at%20Allianz%20Life%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBoomers%20have%20been%20in%20it%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20really%20news.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20fell%20right%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20with%2066%25%20reporting%20that%20they%20fear%20running%20out%20of%20money%20more%20than%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20your%20age%2C%20you%20want%20to%20prepare%20for%20what's%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bfragile%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20five%20years%20before%20and%20the%20five%20years%20right%20after%20you%20retire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20pivotal%20time%20when%20investors%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20market%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20close%20to%20retirement%20or%20at%20retirement%20and%20starting%20to%20take%20money%20out%2C%20it%20could%20devastate%20your%20whole%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20as%20you%20no%20longer%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20time%20in%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20a%20significant%20loss%20because%20of%20the%20market%20and%20you're%20taking%20out%20money%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20that%20could%20be%20the%20difference%20between%20having%20money%20for%20your%20entire%20lifetime%20and%20running%20out%20in%2020%20years%20before%20your%20lifetime%20does%2C%20so%20having%20protection%20against%20those%20variables%20is%20really%20important%20the%20closer%20you%20are%20to%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20millennials%2C%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20and%20boomers%20can%20do%20right%20now%20to%20mitigate%20the%20so-called%20fragile%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d8ebe68-a903-4620-98bd-f0f92f38fa0e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20millennials%2C%20'it's%20all%20about%20putting%20money%20away%20now'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERetirement%20may%20seem%20far%20off%2C%20but%20for%20millennials%20and%20younger%20generations%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20all%20about%20putting%20money%20away%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%20%26quot%3BKeep%20as%20much%20as%20you%20comfortably%20can%2C%20put%20that%20away%2C%20because%20the%20more%20you%20save%20when%20you're%20younger%2C%20the%20further%20ahead%20you'll%20be%20later%20on%2C%20so%20you%20don't%20run%20into%20the%20crisis%20that%20many%20boomers%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simplest%20way%20to%20save%20is%20to%20automatically%20and%20regularly%20transfer%20money%20from%20your%20paycheck%20or%20checking%20account%20to%20your%20retirement%20account.%20If%20you%20never%20see%20the%20money%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20tempted%20to%20spend%20it%2C%20and%20you'll%20learn%20to%20live%20without%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20where%20to%20save%2C%20contribute%20to%20a%20401(k)%20account%20if%20your%20employer%20offers%20one.%20If%20it%20offers%20a%20match%20program%2C%20which%20is%20essentially%20free%20money%2C%20contribute%20at%20least%20enough%20to%20get%20the%20full%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20eligible%20to%20save%20in%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20%E2%80%94%20you%20must%20earn%20less%20than%20%24150%2C000%20as%20an%20individual%20%E2%80%94%20take%20advantage%20of%20that%20account%2C%20said%20LaVigne%3A%20%26quot%3BPutting%20money%20into%20that%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20traditional%20one%20early%20on%20in%20your%20career%20is%20possibly%20one%20of%20the%20better%20opportunities%20for%20you%20to%20be%20in%20good%20shape%20when%20you%20do%20start%20really%20getting%20serious%20about%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c70c0a6-6191-41b9-8d93-09394bc4ac56%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20it's%20'crunch%20time'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERetirement%20is%20right%20around%20the%20corner%20for%20Gen%20X.%20Now%20is%20the%20time%20to%20add%20to%20your%20nest%20egg%20if%20you%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Gen%20Xers%20are%20realizing%20that%20it's%20crunch%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%20Much%20of%20this%20generation%20has%20about%20a%2010-year%20timeframe%20and%20has%20kids%20either%20finishing%20college%20or%20already%20out%20of%20school.%20Especially%20if%20you're%20feeling%20behind%20on%20savings%20or%20realizing%20you%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20work%20as%20long%20as%20you%20wanted%20to%20due%20to%20health%20reasons%2C%20%26quot%3Bnow%20it's%20about%20you%20and%20getting%20serious%20about%20saving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20about%20ways%20you%20can%20boost%20your%20income%2C%20starting%20with%20your%20current%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20depends%20on%20what%20your%20current%20career%20is.%20Can%20you%20get%20more%20out%20of%20doing%20more%20at%20your%20current%20job%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Negotiating%20a%20raise%20or%20picking%20up%20more%20hours%20is%20going%20to%20be%20easier%20than%20starting%20a%20side%20hustle%20or%20part-time%20job%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20have%20the%20interest%20and%20you%20can%20sacrifice%20the%20time%2C%20it%20certainly%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20get%20ahead.%20And%20just%20put%20all%20that%20money%20away.%20Don't%20even%20use%20it%20for%20expenses.%20Put%20as%20much%20as%20you%20possibly%20can%20away%20for%20a%20rainy%20day%20and%20for%20your%20future%20retirement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e7b26b2-cf49-48fa-a18d-b43c21315f4b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20boomers%2C%20understand%20your%20investments%20and%20be%20strategic%20with%20Social%20Security%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20investment%20products%20out%20there%20designed%20to%20mitigate%20risk%20the%20closer%20you%20get%20to%20retirement%2C%20said%20LaVigne%3A%20%26quot%3BThings%20like%20exchange-traded%20funds%2C%20which%20don't%20follow%20an%20individual%20stock.%26quot%3B%20There%20are%20also%20buffer%20ETFs%2C%20which%20can%20limit%20losses%20over%20a%20set%20period.%20%26quot%3BSay%2C%20over%20a%20year%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%2010%25%20loss%2C%20they%20might%20be%20able%20to%20make%20you%20whole%20at%20the%20end%20of%20that%2010%25%20period%20of%20time%2C%20so%20that%20you%20don't%20fall%20behind%20because%20your%20investments%20are%20losing%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-an-annuity%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAnnuities%2520are%2520investment%2520products%2520issued%2Coften%2520rolled%2520into%2520the%2520cost.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannuities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20provide%20a%20guaranteed%20income%20stream%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20give%20you%20some%20growth%2C%20because%20you%20need%20growth%20to%20get%20enough%20money%20for%20retirement%2C%20but%20offer%20you%20protections%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20worse%20to%20lose%20the%20money%20after%20you%20get%20it%20than%20not%20to%20get%20the%20money%20at%20all%2C%20so%20those%20are%20things%20that%20these%20investments%20can%20help%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20approaching%20retirement%2C%20look%20over%20your%20investments%20and%20understand%20exactly%20where%20your%20money%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20also%20want%20to%20strategize%20around%20Social%20Security.%20You%20can%20start%20taking%20it%20as%20early%20as%20age%2062%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20you%20should.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-regrets-401k-divorce-moving-financial-mistakes-aarp-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregret%20taking%20it%20prematurely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20just%20take%20Social%20Security%20because%20you%20turned%2062%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20the%20right%20thing%20for%20you%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20not%20an%20advocate%20for%20everybody%20waiting%20until%20age%2070%20%E2%80%94%20but%20knowing%20the%20rules%20around%20how%20Social%20Security%20works%20is%20a%20really%2C%20really%20important%20part.%20It's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20your%20entire%20retirement%20income%2C%20but%20for%20the%20average%20American%2C%20it%20is%20about%2040%25%20of%20their%20retirement%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20easier%20said%20than%20done%2C%20especially%20amid%20market%20volatility%20that's%20outside%20your%20control%2C%20%26quot%3Boverall%2C%20the%20best%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20not%20panic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStay%20the%20course%2C%20stick%20to%20your%20plan%2C%20and%20don't%20let%20other%20people's%20decisions%20impact%20yours%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20be%20the%20one%20that%20says%2C%20'Oh%2C%20everybody's%20pulling%20their%20money%20out.%20I'm%20going%20to%20pull%20my%20money%20out.'%20And%20then%20six%20months%20or%20two%20years%20later%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20hear%20people%20are%20putting%20their%20money%20in.%20The%20market%20is%20rallying.'%20By%20the%20time%20the%20market's%20rallying%2C%20you've%20already%20missed%20some%20of%20the%20best%20days%20in%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http