0its%20lowest-rated%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20updated%20model%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20distinguishes%26quot%3B%20those%20with%20consistent%20excellence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20always%2C%20employees'%20contributions%20drive%20the%20outcome%20of%20their%20annual%20compensation%20review%2C%26quot%3B%20Amazon's%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20different%20this%20year%20is%20that%20our%20approach%20to%20compensation%20changes%20now%20better%20distinguishes%20between%20newer%20high%20performers%20and%20those%20who%20have%20consistently%20exceeded%20expectations%20for%20their%20role%20and%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b89c241-96dc-41c9-879e-3b07fce98f79%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Overall%20Value'%20ratings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon's%2012-month%20pay%20cycle%20for%20corporate%20employees%20typically%20starts%20in%20April.%20Most%20rank-and-file%20employees%20receive%20their%20pay%20updates%20in%20early%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Amazon%20considers%20various%20factors%20when%20determining%20employee%20pay%2C%20individual%20performance%20ratings%E2%80%94internally%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BOverall%20Value%26quot%3B%E2%80%94are%20a%20key%20driver.%20Employees%20are%20ranked%20across%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-annual-performance-review-process-bonus-salary-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive%20performance%20tiers%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Top%20Tier%20(TT)%2C%20Highly%20Valued%203%20(HV3)%2C%20Highly%20Valued%202%20(HV2)%2C%20Highly%20Valued%201%20(HV1)%2C%20and%20Least%20Effective%20(LE).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internal%20guidelines%20say%20performance%20%26quot%3Bdirectly%20impacts%26quot%3B%20compensation%2C%20and%20the%20OV%20ratings%20are%20%26quot%3Bused%20to%20generate%20the%20compensation%20recommendation%20for%20each%20employee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-wid